<Content title="About" description="What The Kaamo Club is and how it came to be.">
  <h2>What is The Kaamo Club?</h2>
  <p>
    The Kaamo Club is the community hub for the <em>Galaxy on Fire</em> game
    series. It's a single launch point for the official Discord, the subreddit,
    and the wiki.gg page — and a growing set of self-hosted services for
    players and fans.
  </p>
  <p>
    The name comes from the private station hideout in <em>Galaxy on Fire 2</em>,
    where a pilot could dock between missions, store ships, and tinker with
    their gear. The hub is meant to feel the same way: a quiet anchor point
    away from the noise, with everything a Galaxy on Fire fan might want under
    one roof.
  </p>

  <h2>What's here, and what's coming</h2>
  <p>
    The site is being built phase by phase, in the open. The
    <a href="/bays">Docking Bays</a> page lists each "bay" (service or external
    community) with its current status. Bays marked offline will come online as
    they're built.
  </p>

